verbose_text: Taken together, these results suggested that decreased miR-342-3p expression in APPsw-Tg mice endothelium leads to a rise in Chi3l1 expression, resulting in the exacerbation of vascular inflammation and the development of atherosclerosis in APPsw-Tg mice.
evidence: miR-342-3p expression in APPsw-Tg mice endothelium leads to a rise in Chi3l1 expression, resulting in the exacerbation of vascular inflammation
